description:
Many other frog species camouflage themselves in the wild, but the poison dart frog uses its brightly colored skin to warn predators that it is unfit to eat. The frog's skin secretes a dangerous poison that can paralyze and even kill predators. There are more than 100 species of poison dart frogs, including those that live in the Amazon.&nbsp;

<span style="line-height: 1.5em;">Climate change and habitat loss threaten their survival. WWF is working to ensure that their Amazon forest habitat remains intact.</span>

&nbsp;
